value.0: **Motions the other druids to stand down**  You there.  You ... you uphold the balence do you not?
Dont lie to me <Boy/Girl>.  I can see much that you can not.  You do indeed.  Though why you would lie about it is beyond me.  Surely you know what this place is?
**Frowns a bit and mutters something about dilution of the old ways.**  What is your name?
Then you best be leaving.

This <lad/lass> is a Moonpool and through it the beauty and the power of the Earth Mother flows.  It is the most sacared of Her places in these isles.

You may observe the pool.  Though we will be watching.  If you intend any harm to it, you will pay with your lives.
Well earned, no doubt. You have our gratitude.
We certainly do! There are always tasks for the intrepid to carry out in the Mother's name; however, not all are suited to the rigours they demand. Grave peril awaits! Are you up to the challenge?

Good. So then.  The mountains to the north are riddled with caves, and those caves are riddled with abominations. We will not ask you to venture into the lower caverns, for there lie greater evils than even mighty heroes could hope to vanquish.  The upper layers host a plethora of lesser evils; vicious bats that swarm out at night to plague these lands. In number, they are a terrible foe, not to mention a tremendous nuisance.  Your task is to reduce said number. Tread carefully, avoid the deeper reaches at all costs, and travel in force. You will find there is plenty of work to do, and we will reward you for every one of their beastly wings you bring us as proof of success.
Earth Mother bless you. These cursed creatures cannot be allowed to tip the balance She strives for any longer!  But! Be careful; they really are some nasty bloody bats...
What is your name?
Then you best be leaving.
Well then what do you want?
